news.title: Adani Cement's ACC and Ambuja to resume Himachal Pradesh operations
news.para: All stakeholders have amicably resolved the issues on freight rates in the state of Himachal Pradesh, the company said, adding that ACC and Ambuja will resume operations on Tuesday at the Gagal and Darlaghat plants.

news.title: China launches pilot scheme to boost private investment in real estate
news.para: Investors in the scheme, predominantly institutional, should offer no less than 10 million yuan each to participate, the China Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC) said.

news.title: Parsvnath Developers posts net loss of Rs 160.82 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Parsvnath Developers' consolidated total income stood at Rs 87.75 crore in Q3 FY23, a dip of 70.89 per cent from Rs 301.44 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Maha RERA issues show-cause notices to 313 projects for shortcomings
news.para: The shortcomings include total expenditure claimed to be incurred by a developer not reflecting on the ground, it said, pointing out that there are situations where a developer has claimed 75 per cent of the budgeted expenditure is done while the project is only 50 per cent complete.

news.title: Nashik civic body aims to make C&D recycling plant operational in six months
news.para: The Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) has finally identified a plot of land adjacent to the existing civic compost plant in Pathardi, on the outskirts of the city, for this purpose.

news.title: Cluster development policy remains on paper six years after Pune civic body's approval
news.para: The policy has been kept in abeyance though the state government has approved the development plan for civic areas, but. If approved, the cluster development policy would promote the redevelopment of old wadas and smaller properties in Peth areas.

news.title: Hand over five apartments, consumer panel asks developer in Nashik
news.para: The three-bench commission passed its judgement in which it has ordered the developer to construct the apartments with complete amenities as promised and hand them over the consumer after getting the fees required for installation of electrical meter and registration costs.

news.title: REITs, InvITs request govt to review tax on distribution through debt repayment
news.para: As per the Securities & Exchange Board of India’s regulations, both REITs and InvITs are required to distribute their cash surplus up to certain limits on a quarterly basis. These distributions generally consist of interest, dividend, or repayment of debt.

news.title: Residents of Malibu Towne protest, seek Haryana CM's help over ban on registry
news.para: The residents have submitted a memorandum, addressing the chief minister, to SDM Ravinder Yadav seeking his intervention to limit the operation of HSPCB’s order against the developer only.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso residents want flats at same site, refuse to vacate
news.para: On Sunday morning, the residents of towers D, E, F, G and H of the Sector 109 society held a meeting and decided they would not leave the premises unless the administration shared a rehabilitation plan.

news.title: Builders in 705 lapsed projects seek renewal after MahaRERA notice
news.para: ​For the first time in the history of MahaRERA, information about completion of these many projects have been updated on the website in a month's time.

news.title: Kerala government to prepare GIS maps of properties
news.para: LSGD has issued an order for the digital mapping of properties based on the recommendation of the sixth state finance commission (SSFC). There should be separate markings for public and private properties, SSFC had said in its report.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body to set up construction waste processing unit
news.para: The civic body has invited a tender to select an agency that will not only set up the plant but will also be responsible for its operation and maintenance.

news.title: Civic body serves property tax notices on Lucknow mall, hotel
news.para: The LMC officials said that the tax notices were served to the Lulu mall a week ago and to the Centrum hotel in February.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body issues notification to sell 37 plots
news.para: These plots are spread in its various layouts in the combined Visakhapatnam and Vizianagaram districts. The base prices of these plots range between 14,000 and 55,000 depending on the location. Some plots measure as high as 800 square yards.
